column1: Holders of shares of Class A Common Stock and Class  Common Stock have identical rights except that holders of shares of
Class A Common Stock are entitled to one vote per share and holders of shares of Class  Common Stock are entitled to 10 vote
per share. Holders of shares of Class A Common Stock and Class  Common Stock vote together as a single class on all matters
including the election of directors submitted to a vote of stockholders unless otherwise required by law.
